Utilities and software to compute transit spectra from Athena++ simulations of evaporative flows from planets.

Example usage:
python /Users/morganmacleod/Dropbox/PlanetWind/Analysis/planet-wind-rt/Planet_Wind_Ray_Star_Origin23.py --base_dir ./ --level 3 --N_mc 3000 --N_raypoints 200 --angles 0.06 --snapshot PW_W107.out1.00030.athdf --scale 0.25

v24 (as in revised paper):
python /Users/morganmacleod/Dropbox/PlanetWind/Analysis/planet-wind-rt/Planet_Wind_Ray_Star_Origin24.py --base_dir ./ --level 3 --N_radial 100 --f_raystep 0.05  --angles 0.06 --snapshot PW_W107.out1.00030.athdf --scale 0.2


Other example scripts are in the example folders, these are the scripts used to produce the data represented in the publication. 